A vintage-style illustration of a weathered leather journal lying open on a worn wooden desk, its pages filled with handwritten entries and sketches, a fountain pen resting across the spine. Soft afternoon light streams through a nearby window, casting warm golden rays across scattered photographs and postcards from Singapore pinned to a cork board in the background. The journal shows visible wear from years of use, with dog-eared pages and ribbon bookmarks. A steaming cup of tea sits beside the journal, and small potted plants frame the cozy writing nook, evoking a sense of personal reflection and creative milestone.
